This paper is about abstractive summarization, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of reinforcement learning and BERT also suggests a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves optimizing summary-level ROUGE scores, which is a common evaluation metric in NLP, and thus could potentially fall under cs.LG (Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning suggests a focus on optimization and decision-making, which could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
